{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"04e1b6a5-e0c4-44a6-aa56-516cde55a318","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload via `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked through `dotnet run`. When you run:\n\n```\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nthe testing platform starts, watches for file changes, and re-runs affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest adapter and **does not** support hot reload — it runs tests once and exits.\n\nSince you already have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled, you can also use `dotnet test` for one-off runs, but for hot reload you must use `dotnet run`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0bda14be-d5ec-4566-9d37-7489528c7c4d","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"300B:FA277:453FC12:4C1103D:6A031072"},"id":"136d54ae-9bca-4176-b522-46b0209ee124","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:26.043Z","parentId":"b5dbd676-de11-48b6-a10e-5afd31604700"}
